WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.001 --> 00:00:06.001
- Synced and corrected by<font color="#00BFFF"> Firefly</font> -
- <font color="#00ffff">www.addic7ed.com</font> -

2
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:14.074
Free Gift Cards and Tech Items with
Southwest Points: www.fairylandshop.me

3
00:02:31.359 --> 00:02:35.864
You stand before the Queen
of the Seven Kingdoms...

4
00:02:37.449 --> 00:02:40.268
with a dragon of House Targaryen!

5
00:02:41.703 --> 00:02:43.950
I had no design upon it!

6
00:02:43.955 --> 00:02:45.541
What do you want?!

7
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:49.461
To learn the ways of dragonriders.

8
00:02:51.379 --> 00:02:53.181
And to serve my queen!

9
00:02:55.133 --> 00:02:56.397
Your Grace!

10
00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:26.368
You kneel quickly...

11
00:03:26.873 --> 00:03:29.134
for a man so suddenly elevated.

12
00:03:30.043 --> 00:03:33.875
This dragon came to me. not I to him.

13
00:03:36.132 --> 00:03:39.173
I have sweated blood in
service of House Velaryon.

14
00:03:40.178 --> 00:03:42.017
I may appear lowborn...

15
00:03:42.722 --> 00:03:45.300
but I know much and more of service!

16
00:03:47.268 --> 00:03:49.549
And if the gods call
me to greater things.

17
00:03:49.554 --> 00:03:51.222
who am I to refuse them?

18
00:04:00.573 --> 00:04:01.783
Stand.

19
00:04:10.208 --> 00:04:11.871
What is your parentage?

20
00:04:11.876 --> 00:04:13.745
My mother was a shipwright.

21
00:04:15.113 --> 00:04:16.398
My father is...

22
00:04:17.649 --> 00:04:19.067
no one of consequence.

23
00:04:20.218 --> 00:04:23.341
Your ancestors. any of House Targaryen?

24
00:04:23.346 --> 00:04:26.358
We're not the sort of family
to keep annals. Your Grace.

25
00:04:28.810 --> 00:04:30.120
What is your name?

26
00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:33.181
Addam... of Hull.

27
00:04:41.514 --> 00:04:43.325
You have done something...

28
00:04:45.143 --> 00:04:46.745
I feared impossible...

29
00:04:48.688 --> 00:04:50.190
Addam of Hull.

30
00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:56.997
I am glad of it.

31
00:05:01.593 --> 00:05:03.762
Do you think you can
get him to Dragonstone?

32
00:05:06.565 --> 00:05:07.833
I can try.

33
00:05:14.564 --> 00:05:16.603
All my life...

34
00:05:16.608 --> 00:05:20.153
I have endeavored to serve
both my house and the realm.

35
00:05:22.089 --> 00:05:23.799
And somehow none of it matters.

36
00:05:26.451 --> 00:05:27.686
We are cast aside.

37
00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:31.506
Or hated.

38
00:05:34.876 --> 00:05:37.457
You'll have a scar...

39
00:05:37.462 --> 00:05:40.835
but... it will be easily hidden.

40
00:05:46.012 --> 00:05:47.842
Nothing is clean here.

41
00:05:57.649 --> 00:06:00.238
I wish to go out. Ser Rickard.

42
00:06:00.243 --> 00:06:01.482
Out?

43
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:04.050
To the Kingswood. I think.

44
00:06:04.055 --> 00:06:05.585
Then I'll have the stewards prepare

45
00:06:05.590 --> 00:06:07.167
- a retinue.
- No retinue.

46
00:06:08.176 --> 00:06:09.990
- Then your handmaidens...
- No handmaidens.

47
00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.564
Just you.

48
00:06:22.799 --> 00:06:25.844
What are they for? The
block or the crow cage?

49
00:06:26.678 --> 00:06:28.263
The Wall.

50
00:06:29.180 --> 00:06:31.011
The prince regent is merciful.

51
00:06:31.016 --> 00:06:32.058
Hm.

52
00:06:33.935 --> 00:06:36.641
Well. they started a riot.

53
00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:38.924
Justice is served. I suppose.

54
00:06:47.032 --> 00:06:50.131
I have received word of a
matter of great importance.

55
00:06:51.536 --> 00:06:54.414
Rumor of a sighting of
the dragon Seasmoke...

56
00:06:55.707 --> 00:06:57.292
with a rider.

57
00:06:58.418 --> 00:07:00.665
A fine piece of intelligence.

58
00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:04.377
and now you seek favor by
delivering it to Prince Aemond.

59
00:07:04.382 --> 00:07:07.981
Actually. I thought I might
seek your advice. Lord Larys.

60
00:07:07.986 --> 00:07:10.030
Whispers being your province.

61
00:07:10.972 --> 00:07:14.642
Kneel before the Prince
Regent Aemond Targaryen!

62
00:07:15.226 --> 00:07:17.223
Oh. but this is your whisper.

63
00:07:17.228 --> 00:07:19.293
Lord Jasper. not mine.

64
00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:21.971
But if you consider it valuable...

65
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:25.023
perhaps you could deliver it

66
00:07:25.028 --> 00:07:27.142
and find favor with Aemond yourself.

67
00:07:27.147 --> 00:07:29.903
You will forsake your
white cloaks for black.

68
00:07:29.908 --> 00:07:32.739
serve out your days at The Wall.

69
00:07:32.744 --> 00:07:34.741
Who is this rider?

70
00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:37.744
That is less clear.

71
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:39.605
but it must surely be the Lady Rhaena.

72
00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:41.956
She has wanted for
a dragon all her life.

73
00:07:41.961 --> 00:07:43.583
Indeed. but she tried already

74
00:07:43.588 --> 00:07:44.793
when she was four and ten.

75
00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:46.961
The beast Seasmoke
very nearly devoured her.

76
00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:48.243
Who else?

77
00:07:49.761 --> 00:07:52.592
Yes. it is a shallow pool.

78
00:07:52.597 --> 00:07:54.427
Where did you hear it?

79
00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:55.684
My squire.

80
00:07:57.435 --> 00:07:59.933
He heard it from a stablehand.

81
00:07:59.938 --> 00:08:02.478
who heard it from
his father. a fisherman.

82
00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:05.719
whose shipmate claims he saw it.

83
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:08.029
Oh.

84
00:08:11.616 --> 00:08:13.947
You are. of course.
welcome to bring this news

85
00:08:13.952 --> 00:08:16.221
to the prince regent. but. um...

86
00:08:17.455 --> 00:08:20.726
perhaps this is one of those
whispers best left to the wind.

87
00:09:01.374 --> 00:09:03.255
The queen is unharmed.

88
00:09:03.260 --> 00:09:05.507
What of the rider? Do we know who he is?

89
00:09:06.212 --> 00:09:08.043
He appears to be a shipwright

90
00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:10.003
in your employ. Lord Hand.

91
00:09:10.008 --> 00:09:11.546
A commoner?

92
00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:14.132
With respect to your
workers. Lord Corlys.

93
00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:18.178
the lowborn cannot go
around seizing dragons.

94
00:09:18.183 --> 00:09:20.305
Has the thief been secured?

95
00:09:20.310 --> 00:09:23.641
Her Grace has commanded
that he remain here as a guest.

96
00:09:23.646 --> 00:09:25.185
She wishes him to be instructed

97
00:09:25.190 --> 00:09:27.687
in the art of dragonriding.

98
00:09:27.692 --> 00:09:30.190
and that I should teach
him some High Valyrian.

99
00:09:30.695 --> 00:09:32.817
We know nothing about this man.

100
00:09:32.822 --> 00:09:34.569
save that he is lowborn.

101
00:09:34.574 --> 00:09:36.468
What say you. Lord Hand?

102
00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:40.205
We will await the queen's accounting...

103
00:09:41.289 --> 00:09:43.884
before passing judgment.

104
00:09:46.444 --> 00:09:47.662
Where is the queen?

105
00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:52.384
Her Grace sends word
she will not be attending.

106
00:09:56.888 --> 00:09:59.516
So he serves you and not himself.

107
00:09:59.808 --> 00:10:01.889
- That is lucky.
- Lucky?

108
00:10:02.394 --> 00:10:03.937
Or somehow ordained?

109
00:10:04.646 --> 00:10:06.393
Seasmoke chose him.

110
00:10:06.398 --> 00:10:09.729
He surely has Targaryen
blood in him somewhere.

111
00:10:09.734 --> 00:10:11.022
The dragon must sense it.

112
00:10:11.027 --> 00:10:12.107
There will be others.

113
00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:13.191
We will find riders

114
00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:14.276
for Vermithor and Silverwing.

115
00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:15.657
You trust this man?

116
00:10:16.574 --> 00:10:18.029
What choice do I have?

117
00:10:18.034 --> 00:10:19.447
He has a dragon.

118
00:10:19.452 --> 00:10:21.032
Without him. I have only Syrax

119
00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:23.110
who may give Aemond a second thought.

120
00:10:23.915 --> 00:10:25.959
The question is where to look.

121
00:10:26.501 --> 00:10:30.542
Targaryen blood was perhaps
too thin in Ser Steffon Darklyn.

122
00:10:30.547 --> 00:10:32.877
If I can find others
with a more direct line

123
00:10:32.882 --> 00:10:34.893
of breeding.

124
00:10:35.969 --> 00:10:37.629
Forgive me. Your Grace...

125
00:10:40.432 --> 00:10:41.677
but you are better served

126
00:10:41.682 --> 00:10:44.607
looking under the sheets
and in the woodpiles.

127
00:10:48.606 --> 00:10:50.478
I once worked in a pleasure house

128
00:10:50.483 --> 00:10:54.774
where generations of Targaryen
princelings had their revels.

129
00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:58.278
There are four score of their
bastard progeny at least.

130
00:10:58.283 --> 00:10:59.946
that are known to me.

131
00:10:59.951 --> 00:11:02.115
There are sure to be more.

132
00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:04.117
Perhaps some here. on Dragonstone.

133
00:11:04.122 --> 00:11:07.209
the misbegotten offspring of your house.

134
00:11:17.552 --> 00:11:19.090
You speak of the lowborn.

135
00:11:19.095 --> 00:11:20.675
They are as like to serve you

136
00:11:20.680 --> 00:11:23.742
as highborn lords or
ladies. perhaps more.

137
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:29.642
But in the highborn houses there is...

138
00:11:29.647 --> 00:11:32.233
an ancient fealty.

139
00:11:33.234 --> 00:11:34.286
There is honor.

140
00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:38.693
Your royal half-brothers.
Aegon and Aemond.

141
00:11:38.698 --> 00:11:43.745
whose blood is pure. who wage
war against you for your throne.

142
00:11:44.662 --> 00:11:46.206
are they bound by honor?

143
00:11:51.836 --> 00:11:55.543
A common shipwright vows to serve you

144
00:11:55.548 --> 00:11:58.193
while your brothers seek to destroy you.

145
00:12:00.345 --> 00:12:03.865
The order of things has
changed. Your Grace.

146
00:12:05.225 --> 00:12:06.760
Why not embrace it?

147
00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:19.859
For 20 years. the lords
of this realm levied...

148
00:12:19.864 --> 00:12:23.335
insults at my sons behind my back.

149
00:12:31.126 --> 00:12:32.377
Well then.

150
00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:36.648
Let us raise an army of bastards.

151
00:12:57.736 --> 00:12:59.805
- My lord.
- "My lord"?

152
00:13:00.947 --> 00:13:02.958
How you have come up in the world.

153
00:13:05.577 --> 00:13:07.615
I wish to ask for leave
to relinquish my part

154
00:13:07.620 --> 00:13:09.868
as a shipwright in your service.

155
00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:12.425
There are good men and strong
who can take my place...

156
00:13:17.489 --> 00:13:18.758
Your leave is granted.

157
00:13:31.770 --> 00:13:32.971
Well done.

158
00:14:01.725 --> 00:14:04.297
Lord Tully has answered
your summons and brought

159
00:14:04.302 --> 00:14:06.321
the Riverlords. my king.

160
00:14:12.018 --> 00:14:14.941
My condolences on the
passing of your grandsire

161
00:14:14.946 --> 00:14:16.386
but the crown congratulates you

162
00:14:16.391 --> 00:14:17.978
on your ascension to
the head of your house

163
00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:19.688
and Lord Paramount in the Riverlands.

164
00:14:19.693 --> 00:14:21.152
Truly glorious. Well done.

165
00:14:22.237 --> 00:14:24.361
- I did nothing.
- Nevertheless.

166
00:14:24.365 --> 00:14:26.653
you are here. which
is the important thing.

167
00:14:26.658 --> 00:14:28.488
You were quick enough
to dismiss me before.

168
00:14:28.493 --> 00:14:30.949
You were of no significance to me then.

169
00:14:30.954 --> 00:14:32.163
Now...

170
00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:36.877
I shall have my great host.

171
00:14:38.278 --> 00:14:40.292
You have a decision to make.

172
00:14:40.797 --> 00:14:42.966
I presume it is clear to you
which is the right one.

173
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:45.714
You'll forgive me. Your Grace.

174
00:14:45.719 --> 00:14:47.841
I am green in this sort of matter.

175
00:14:47.846 --> 00:14:51.937
as you so kindly point out. but...

176
00:14:52.642 --> 00:14:56.141
it does seem to me that you've
made rather a mess here.

177
00:14:56.146 --> 00:15:00.145
countenancing barbarities
in the queen's name.

178
00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:01.693
Whose side are you on?

179
00:15:06.740 --> 00:15:09.543
The Riverlands are
held together by oaths.

180
00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:14.840
House Tully swore
an oath to King Viserys.

181
00:15:16.775 --> 00:15:18.246
We recognize the authority

182
00:15:18.251 --> 00:15:20.512
of the named heir. Queen Rhaenyra

183
00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:24.724
and your own... as her king consort.

184
00:15:26.159 --> 00:15:27.369
Good.

185
00:15:28.787 --> 00:15:30.342
Then we shall go to face your vassals

186
00:15:30.347 --> 00:15:31.761
and you will call your banners to war.

187
00:15:31.765 --> 00:15:33.659
That might be difficult. my king.

188
00:15:39.047 --> 00:15:40.298
Well...

189
00:15:41.800 --> 00:15:43.396
I was told they would come to heel

190
00:15:43.401 --> 00:15:45.732
when House Tully
declared its allegiance.

191
00:15:45.737 --> 00:15:47.326
That may be the case.

192
00:15:48.031 --> 00:15:50.737
though it is yet to be seen that
they will heed my authority

193
00:15:50.742 --> 00:15:52.244
as young as it is.

194
00:15:54.329 --> 00:15:56.089
And there is another problem.

195
00:15:58.416 --> 00:16:00.121
They all hate you.

196
00:16:03.588 --> 00:16:05.460
I don't need their love.

197
00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:07.545
I need their swords.

198
00:16:10.095 --> 00:16:14.094
Your Grace. my lord.
The Riverlords await.

199
00:16:14.099 --> 00:16:16.176
I fear we cannot delay them any longer.

200
00:16:23.149 --> 00:16:25.160
Come along. Lord Oscar.

201
00:16:48.049 --> 00:16:50.343
In the deepest darkness comes the dawn.

202
00:16:51.136 --> 00:16:52.465
A new lord.

203
00:16:52.470 --> 00:16:54.180
a new beginning.

204
00:16:55.348 --> 00:16:57.892
Let us put all the old
unpleasantness behind us.

205
00:17:03.982 --> 00:17:05.784
Be welcome. my lords...

206
00:17:07.152 --> 00:17:09.975
and you have my thanks
for answering my summons.

207
00:17:10.380 --> 00:17:12.986
I know I'm not the man my grandsire was.

208
00:17:12.991 --> 00:17:17.266
but I hope to begin well.
and go on from there.

209
00:17:17.871 --> 00:17:20.957
Well said. One thing is clear...

210
00:17:21.608 --> 00:17:24.631
the Rivermen honor the old
ways and abide by tradition.

211
00:17:24.636 --> 00:17:26.433
Here. then. is tradition.

212
00:17:26.838 --> 00:17:28.376
Grover Tully is dead.

213
00:17:28.381 --> 00:17:30.337
Lord Oscar raised up in his place.

214
00:17:30.342 --> 00:17:32.005
You have been summoned here

215
00:17:32.010 --> 00:17:33.882
to swear anew your fealty to him.

216
00:17:33.887 --> 00:17:37.844
and as his bannermen. answer his call.

217
00:17:37.849 --> 00:17:40.180
And what would that call be?

218
00:17:40.185 --> 00:17:42.182
In his wisdom. he has pledged his house.

219
00:17:42.187 --> 00:17:43.559
and yours. to me.

220
00:17:46.024 --> 00:17:49.356
Lord Oscar. for generations
we have been guided

221
00:17:49.361 --> 00:17:51.446
by the judgment of your forebears.

222
00:17:51.863 --> 00:17:55.236
Why should we now follow a boy.
younger than my own sons.

223
00:17:55.241 --> 00:17:56.696
when you will align with one

224
00:17:56.701 --> 00:17:58.907
who will desecrate the
innocent to reach his aims?

225
00:18:00.413 --> 00:18:03.308
I did only what was necessary. my lord.

226
00:18:04.793 --> 00:18:06.915
And I now deliver to you the traitor

227
00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:09.134
Amos Bracken and his son.

228
00:18:09.139 --> 00:18:11.954
No more traitor to his land
than you. Willem Blackwood.

229
00:18:13.259 --> 00:18:15.840
I take to heart your words. Lord Piper.

230
00:18:15.845 --> 00:18:18.890
and I agree. I-I-I am young.

231
00:18:21.976 --> 00:18:25.266
And I have no love for Daemon Targaryen.

232
00:18:25.271 --> 00:18:27.816
He has dishonored himself
and the crown with his...

233
00:18:29.401 --> 00:18:30.911
comportment here.

234
00:18:32.404 --> 00:18:36.403
Nevertheless. having so
little experience to guide me.

235
00:18:36.408 --> 00:18:40.240
my best course is to defer to
the oath my grandsire swore

236
00:18:40.245 --> 00:18:43.515
to King Viserys when he
named Rhaenyra his heir.

237
00:18:47.168 --> 00:18:49.950
I see no reason to cast aside loyalty

238
00:18:50.755 --> 00:18:54.379
no matter how loathsome I may
find her representative the prince.

239
00:18:54.384 --> 00:18:55.593
King.

240
00:18:56.594 --> 00:18:58.271
Mind your tongue. boy.

241
00:19:10.483 --> 00:19:12.761
Will you have our army or not?

242
00:19:23.496 --> 00:19:25.519
I am. in the end. a Riverman

243
00:19:26.124 --> 00:19:28.413
and the word of my house stands.

244
00:19:28.418 --> 00:19:31.166
even if certain people
are unworthy of it.

245
00:19:38.970 --> 00:19:40.989
Your Lord Oscar is bold.

246
00:19:42.807 --> 00:19:44.839
But he is perhaps not wrong.

247
00:19:46.144 --> 00:19:48.808
I may have been a touch enthusiastic

248
00:19:48.813 --> 00:19:50.315
in pursuing my aims.

249
00:19:51.816 --> 00:19:53.835
But don't allow my failings to...

250
00:19:55.236 --> 00:19:58.443
keep you from supporting an upright man.

251
00:19:58.448 --> 00:20:01.154
Lord Oscar. we honor the old ways.

252
00:20:01.159 --> 00:20:02.698
as Prince Daemon says

253
00:20:03.703 --> 00:20:07.118
- and the old ways call for justice to be done.
- Yes!

254
00:20:07.123 --> 00:20:08.796
Justice has been done.

255
00:20:09.401 --> 00:20:13.297
They who bent the knee to the
usurper have been brought to heel.

256
00:20:14.673 --> 00:20:18.894
And now. we unite
before our liege lord...

257
00:20:20.929 --> 00:20:22.781
and our king consort.

258
00:20:37.362 --> 00:20:40.432
I accept you as my vassal.
Willem Blackwood...

259
00:20:48.206 --> 00:20:49.290
but...

260
00:20:50.959 --> 00:20:54.012
I am Lord Paramount of all River Houses.

261
00:20:56.131 --> 00:20:57.852
And there is only one
answer for the crimes

262
00:20:57.857 --> 00:20:59.484
you visited upon your neighbors.

263
00:21:03.596 --> 00:21:07.721
I did only what His Grace
the king required of me.

264
00:21:07.726 --> 00:21:11.099
It is true that he made
clear his base desires.

265
00:21:11.104 --> 00:21:14.199
but you did not have to
pursue such savagery.

266
00:21:15.608 --> 00:21:19.229
You did it... because you wanted to.

267
00:21:19.779 --> 00:21:21.815
Our young lord speaks truly.

268
00:21:23.825 --> 00:21:26.027
Seize him.

269
00:21:27.212 --> 00:21:29.081
Don't fuckin' do this.

270
00:21:30.915 --> 00:21:33.418
Your Grace. command them.
I've only served you.

271
00:21:38.757 --> 00:21:40.754
- Command them.
- If His Grace wishes

272
00:21:40.759 --> 00:21:43.256
to show contrition for his acts

273
00:21:43.261 --> 00:21:46.294
and to prove himself
deserving of our banners

274
00:21:47.599 --> 00:21:50.305
he must now rectify his grievous error.

275
00:21:50.310 --> 00:21:52.371
Denounce your crimes...

276
00:21:54.022 --> 00:21:56.449
and dispense justice.

277
00:21:58.193 --> 00:21:59.272
Oh. dear.

278
00:22:12.257 --> 00:22:13.859
No. no. no!

279
00:22:14.959 --> 00:22:17.857
I did as you asked. Your
Grace. I have been faithful.

280
00:23:37.459 --> 00:23:38.961
What is this?

281
00:23:41.379 --> 00:23:42.948
I never wanted it.

282
00:23:46.217 --> 00:23:47.728
I was right not to.

283
00:23:52.265 --> 00:23:54.493
All that pain it caused.

284
00:23:58.563 --> 00:24:01.275
It crushes whoever wears it.

285
00:24:05.779 --> 00:24:08.006
You always wanted it. Daemon.

286
00:24:13.912 --> 00:24:15.931
Do you want it still?

287
00:24:25.965 --> 00:24:28.593
Steady. Slowly.

288
00:24:31.930 --> 00:24:33.259
I can't.

289
00:24:33.264 --> 00:24:35.534
You can. You must try. Your Grace.

290
00:24:44.484 --> 00:24:46.773
I can't. I can't!

291
00:24:51.449 --> 00:24:53.613
I'm sorry. Your Grace.
I'm sorry. Your Grace.

292
00:24:53.618 --> 00:24:56.287
Oh. God. Oh. God.

293
00:24:57.122 --> 00:24:58.284
A moment!

294
00:24:58.289 --> 00:25:00.954
A moment. please!

295
00:25:04.713 --> 00:25:08.253
You really oughtn't to be doing
that alone. Grand Maester.

296
00:25:15.974 --> 00:25:17.303
Allow me.

297
00:25:20.061 --> 00:25:21.563
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

298
00:25:21.963 --> 00:25:23.590
Forgive me. Your Grace.

299
00:25:35.368 --> 00:25:37.824
- Be careful.
- Wait. wait.

300
00:25:48.423 --> 00:25:50.475
Your progress is impressive.

301
00:25:52.510 --> 00:25:55.564
But I'm afraid you must work harder.

302
00:25:57.766 --> 00:25:59.846
Your strength will return.

303
00:25:59.851 --> 00:26:02.182
There are... adjustments

304
00:26:02.187 --> 00:26:03.850
to the gait and so forth

305
00:26:03.855 --> 00:26:06.124
that you will learn now that you are...

306
00:26:07.792 --> 00:26:08.897
as you are.

307
00:26:22.082 --> 00:26:24.125
You should be more cautious.

308
00:26:24.542 --> 00:26:26.998
I. I should. Lord Larys.

309
00:26:27.003 --> 00:26:29.501
He-He needs rest. He should be abed.

310
00:26:29.506 --> 00:26:31.603
I push him on your instruction.

311
00:26:32.308 --> 00:26:34.319
I'll have the sentry
give you more warning.

312
00:26:36.805 --> 00:26:38.426
Let him try again in a few hours.

313
00:26:38.431 --> 00:26:39.974
He is spent.

314
00:26:43.228 --> 00:26:45.730
It will be long before
he may rest again.

315
00:26:58.143 --> 00:26:59.211
Alyn.

316
00:27:02.580 --> 00:27:03.998
My lord.

317
00:27:07.193 --> 00:27:09.863
I have tasks that need
your personal attention.

318
00:27:10.422 --> 00:27:13.128
The queen requires ships at
her service in King's Landing.

319
00:27:13.133 --> 00:27:15.922
Charter fishing vessels.
Pay whatever they demand

320
00:27:15.927 --> 00:27:18.930
but ensure their captains
are dependable.

321
00:27:21.433 --> 00:27:23.763
- Put trusted swords aboard.
- Yes. m'lord.

322
00:27:23.768 --> 00:27:25.557
Have them wait just outside the harbor.

323
00:27:25.562 --> 00:27:28.140
And there will be a message
to carry to one she will name.

324
00:27:35.447 --> 00:27:39.480
The queen has found a new
rider for one of her dragons.

325
00:27:40.285 --> 00:27:41.853
I've heard tell of it.

326
00:27:42.787 --> 00:27:44.039
The rider is your brother.

327
00:27:48.710 --> 00:27:50.929
She now makes the call for others.

328
00:27:51.713 --> 00:27:53.960
Our people are of Old Valyria.

329
00:27:53.965 --> 00:27:57.185
but... we are no dragonlords.

330
00:27:59.137 --> 00:28:04.017
I confess. I knew little
of your mother's heritage.

331
00:28:06.561 --> 00:28:08.046
If it is...

332
00:28:09.214 --> 00:28:11.016
something in the blood.

333
00:28:16.196 --> 00:28:18.693
My brother was ever restless.

334
00:28:18.698 --> 00:28:21.168
yearning for some sign of his worth.

335
00:28:22.727 --> 00:28:24.596
I am of salt and sea.

336
00:28:25.872 --> 00:28:27.766
I yearn for nothing else.

337
00:30:29.496 --> 00:30:31.506
I will retire now. Ser Rickard.

338
00:30:39.130 --> 00:30:42.167
When does Your Grace
mean to return to the city?

339
00:30:44.344 --> 00:30:45.846
I'm not yet certain I do.

340
00:30:48.139 --> 00:30:49.140
Good night.

341
00:30:57.816 --> 00:31:00.855
The lowborn claiming dragons.

342
00:31:00.860 --> 00:31:02.649
was it her idea?

343
00:31:02.654 --> 00:31:04.651
Lady Mysaria?

344
00:31:04.656 --> 00:31:07.946
You were enthusiastic enough
when Ser Steffon made his claim.

345
00:31:07.951 --> 00:31:10.031
He was the Lord Commander
of your Queensguard.

346
00:31:10.036 --> 00:31:12.492
Heir to the Dun Fort.
These people are...

347
00:31:12.497 --> 00:31:13.748
Courageous.

348
00:31:14.416 --> 00:31:15.842
Mongrels.

349
00:31:21.715 --> 00:31:22.924
Jace.

350
00:31:25.927 --> 00:31:27.841
Think what is at stake.

351
00:31:27.846 --> 00:31:30.390
I know well what is at stake.

352
00:31:32.934 --> 00:31:35.557
House Targaryen is
the blood of the dragon.

353
00:31:35.562 --> 00:31:38.273
If any may lay claim
to it. what are we then?

354
00:31:38.815 --> 00:31:41.393
The rightful rulers of
the Seven Kingdoms.

355
00:31:42.193 --> 00:31:45.859
And what if one of your baseborn.
silver-haired dragonriders

356
00:31:45.864 --> 00:31:48.653
decides he wants to rule
the Seven Kingdoms?

357
00:31:48.658 --> 00:31:50.677
Did the Conqueror's dream foretell that?

358
00:31:52.078 --> 00:31:54.606
What else would you have me do?

359
00:31:56.624 --> 00:31:58.496
Prosecute a war. which we will lose.

360
00:31:58.501 --> 00:32:00.582
in which thousands will die.

361
00:32:01.087 --> 00:32:03.168
Or fly against Vhagar myself?

362
00:32:03.173 --> 00:32:06.393
Or perhaps you will fly
against her on Vermax.

363
00:32:09.262 --> 00:32:13.292
Jace. with these riders.
we can end a needless war.

364
00:32:15.143 --> 00:32:17.682
I may take my rightful place
on my father's throne.

365
00:32:17.687 --> 00:32:19.264
And when you die?

366
00:32:23.610 --> 00:32:25.620
You are my heir.

367
00:32:39.751 --> 00:32:42.128
Did you think I would have dark hair?

368
00:32:50.303 --> 00:32:52.759
When you took Harwin
Strong into your bed.

369
00:32:52.764 --> 00:32:54.194
did you think I might favor him.

370
00:32:54.199 --> 00:32:55.742
or did it not cross your mind?

371
00:32:58.211 --> 00:33:00.814
- Jacaerys...
- I'm no fool. Mother!

372
00:33:01.981 --> 00:33:03.792
The proof is here for all to see.

373
00:33:06.986 --> 00:33:09.234
Yet I may argue my
legitimacy to succeed you

374
00:33:09.239 --> 00:33:10.782
because I have a dragon.

375
00:33:14.536 --> 00:33:16.788
And now you say you will
strip that from me too.

376
00:33:32.971 --> 00:33:35.540
I mislike all of this.

377
00:33:37.742 --> 00:33:39.319
Then don't pursue it.

378
00:33:47.861 --> 00:33:51.609
But I cannot gainsay that which the gods

379
00:33:51.614 --> 00:33:53.158
have laid before me.

380
00:34:18.558 --> 00:34:21.570
Do whatever you must
to see that it finds her.

381
00:34:47.946 --> 00:34:49.231
From the queen.

382
00:35:36.636 --> 00:35:38.258
You won't believe this.

383
00:35:40.098 --> 00:35:42.137
Word is. Rhaenyra's recruiting

384
00:35:42.142 --> 00:35:44.055
smallfolk to go to Dragonstone.

385
00:35:44.060 --> 00:35:46.725
- Oh. fuck that.
- Oh. they wouldn't take you anyway.

386
00:35:49.107 --> 00:35:52.377
They're looking... for
Targaryen bastards.

387
00:35:53.361 --> 00:35:55.400
Boats leave tonight. Hour of the bat.

388
00:35:55.405 --> 00:35:58.737
Seven hells. Ulf. This is it!

389
00:35:58.742 --> 00:36:00.313
Yeah. a likely story.

390
00:36:00.318 --> 00:36:02.782
- You've been taken in. lads.
- No. no. no. no. no.

391
00:36:02.787 --> 00:36:05.377
The queen's own handmaid
is here. spreadin' the word.

392
00:36:05.382 --> 00:36:07.121
Well. that's a shame
'cause I'd have been

393
00:36:07.125 --> 00:36:09.556
first in line if it
wasn't for my injury.

394
00:36:09.561 --> 00:36:12.125
- 'Cause my leg hasn't been the same since...
- Are you touched?

395
00:36:12.130 --> 00:36:14.252
He's saying you can claim a dragon.

396
00:36:14.257 --> 00:36:16.671
The barkeep from the
Seven Maesters is goin'.

397
00:36:16.676 --> 00:36:18.340
And two of the girls from Mother's.

398
00:36:18.345 --> 00:36:21.176
- A chance to stick it to Aemond.
- And claim a dragon.

399
00:36:21.181 --> 00:36:23.345
- Dragon!
- Yeah. no. I know.

400
00:36:23.350 --> 00:36:25.619
- What?
- I know. I just... I can't...

401
00:36:26.895 --> 00:36:28.747
I can't be sure it's all true.

402
00:36:32.450 --> 00:36:35.524
You can't mean that you've been drinkin'

403
00:36:36.029 --> 00:36:38.643
at the expense of all
these. these good people

404
00:36:38.648 --> 00:36:40.528
- for a fiction? No. Ulf.
- No. no. Shh.

405
00:36:40.533 --> 00:36:42.389
All spark and no tinder?

406
00:36:42.394 --> 00:36:44.158
- They won't be happy.
- They'll be very unhappy.

407
00:36:44.162 --> 00:36:46.326
- Never live it down.
- Never live it down.

408
00:36:46.331 --> 00:36:48.662
- Come on. Ulf. the time has come!
- Come on!

409
00:36:48.667 --> 00:36:50.205
Can I see a little glimmer?

410
00:36:50.210 --> 00:36:52.507
- Where is it?
- There's the Ulf I know.

411
00:36:52.512 --> 00:36:54.576
Yes! Yes. there he is!

412
00:36:54.581 --> 00:36:58.546
- Yes. yes!
- Wine! Wine for Ulf the Dragonlord!

413
00:36:58.551 --> 00:37:00.840
Ulf the Dragonlord!

414
00:37:00.845 --> 00:37:04.678
Ulf the Dragonlord! Ulf the Dragonlord!

415
00:37:15.860 --> 00:37:18.358
I don't want you to go.

416
00:37:18.363 --> 00:37:20.235
I have to. Kat.

417
00:37:20.240 --> 00:37:22.153
We'll go to my brother in Tumbleton.

418
00:37:22.158 --> 00:37:24.731
They'll have food. You'll find work.

419
00:37:24.736 --> 00:37:26.366
I can't ignore this.

420
00:37:30.792 --> 00:37:32.319
I never knew my father.

421
00:37:34.921 --> 00:37:36.423
That much is true.

422
00:37:41.261 --> 00:37:42.763
But I did know my mother.

423
00:37:55.900 --> 00:37:57.136
I hid it from you.

424
00:37:58.570 --> 00:38:00.072
And I'm sorry for that.

425
00:38:04.476 --> 00:38:06.061
She worked...

426
00:38:07.554 --> 00:38:08.763
in a pleasure house.

427
00:38:10.415 --> 00:38:12.438
She was granted more freedom than most

428
00:38:13.043 --> 00:38:14.703
because of who she was.

429
00:38:18.173 --> 00:38:21.176
And because rich men paid more
to fuck a woman with silver hair.

430
00:38:25.764 --> 00:38:26.999
She used to tell me...

431
00:38:28.933 --> 00:38:31.545
I was no different to her brother's boys

432
00:38:34.314 --> 00:38:36.817
Viserys... and Daemon.

433
00:38:43.156 --> 00:38:44.658
But I was ashamed of her.

434
00:38:48.203 --> 00:38:50.706
I tried to make my way
with my own hands.

435
00:38:55.960 --> 00:38:57.533
I could not protect you.

436
00:38:58.838 --> 00:39:01.800
I could not keep our girl alive.

437
00:39:09.374 --> 00:39:10.584
And now...

438
00:39:12.519 --> 00:39:15.542
we would never want again.

439
00:39:16.147 --> 00:39:17.766
If I claimed a dragon...

440
00:39:19.901 --> 00:39:21.940
they'd make you a lady.

441
00:39:27.392 --> 00:39:29.961
I do not care to be a lady. Hugh.

442
00:39:33.081 --> 00:39:35.500
And neither do I want to be a widow.

443
00:39:43.216 --> 00:39:45.277
I have to do somethin'.

444
00:43:46.084 --> 00:43:49.688
I used to think I knew what it
was to claim a dragon. but...

445
00:43:54.843 --> 00:43:57.178
I understand now that
what I thought I knew is...

446
00:43:57.996 --> 00:43:59.564
ash in the wind.

447
00:44:12.218 --> 00:44:13.779
Perhaps it is blood.

448
00:44:14.679 --> 00:44:15.956
Or worth.

449
00:44:17.157 --> 00:44:19.167
Or perhaps it's something else.

450
00:44:24.039 --> 00:44:29.611
Each of you... has left behind
a life to answer this call.

451
00:44:31.046 --> 00:44:35.584
A life to which... you
might never return.

452
00:44:37.844 --> 00:44:40.847
If you survive. you will be transformed.

453
00:44:42.182 --> 00:44:45.777
No man or woman can face
a dragon and be otherwise.

454
00:44:51.691 --> 00:44:55.315
Some of you may welcome
the prospect of change.

455
00:44:55.320 --> 00:44:58.790
even death. given the alternatives:

456
00:44:59.407 --> 00:45:03.461
privation... starvation. war.

457
00:45:04.662 --> 00:45:06.918
This is our purpose.

458
00:45:06.923 --> 00:45:09.134
to end those hardships.

459
00:45:11.169 --> 00:45:12.587
For you...

460
00:45:14.089 --> 00:45:16.984
for your kin. for all the realm.

461
00:45:18.677 --> 00:45:22.842
With these two dragons
added to our number.

462
00:45:22.847 --> 00:45:25.417
the enemy will have no
choice but to give way.

463
00:45:27.018 --> 00:45:29.288
And peace will be restored...

464
00:45:32.023 --> 00:45:35.089
suffering will be ended.

465
00:45:35.694 --> 00:45:38.263
and without bloodshed...

466
00:45:39.531 --> 00:45:41.033
gods willing.

467
00:45:56.423 --> 00:45:57.949
The dragon

468
00:45:58.717 --> 00:46:00.219
named Vermithor...

469
00:46:02.303 --> 00:46:05.844
is the largest in the
world after Vhagar.

470
00:46:05.849 --> 00:46:09.077
and... perhaps. the most fierce.

471
00:46:13.732 --> 00:46:15.937
He's called the Bronze Fury.

472
00:46:22.115 --> 00:46:23.642
We'll go to him now.

473
00:46:25.910 --> 00:46:27.120
And...

474
00:46:30.665 --> 00:46:32.192
may the gods bless you.

475
00:49:34.683 --> 00:49:36.768
Who among you would be first?

476
00:50:06.673 --> 00:50:08.670
I have nothing more to tell you.

477
00:50:08.675 --> 00:50:10.936
It must be the dragon who speaks.

478
00:51:45.530 --> 00:51:47.608
- Your Grace. we must away!
- No.

479
00:52:23.977 --> 00:52:25.779
Help me! Help...

480
00:52:26.504 --> 00:52:27.714
Help me!

481
00:53:15.303 --> 00:53:16.554
Oh. f...

482
00:53:55.610 --> 00:53:57.649
- No!
- Shh. shh. shh!

483
00:54:57.714 --> 00:55:00.754
Here! Here I am!

484
00:55:13.521 --> 00:55:14.934
I'm ready.

485
00:55:30.538 --> 00:55:33.762
Come on!

486
00:59:19.926 --> 00:59:23.484
"Lord Ormund Hightower
makes slow progress.

487
00:59:24.189 --> 00:59:26.419
There is great concern that his host

488
00:59:26.424 --> 00:59:27.729
is threatened on two fronts

489
00:59:27.734 --> 00:59:30.291
by armies allied with House Beesbury".

490
00:59:33.740 --> 00:59:36.154
However. in happier tidings.

491
00:59:36.159 --> 00:59:37.822
Prince Daeron's dragon. Tessarion.

492
00:59:37.827 --> 00:59:39.657
has at last taken to wing.

493
00:59:39.662 --> 00:59:42.077
Your brother expects
to join the fight soon.

494
00:59:42.082 --> 00:59:43.967
Dragon!

495
00:59:44.542 --> 00:59:46.164
And when he does.

496
00:59:46.169 --> 00:59:48.833
the Hightower host will be unstoppable.

497
00:59:48.838 --> 00:59:51.878
Dragon! Inside! Now!

498
01:00:06.231 --> 01:00:08.228
Take positions!

499
01:00:47.105 --> 01:00:48.668
Open the gates!

500
01:03:05.248 --> 01:03:12.748
